The paper describes the development of an artificial neural network (ANN) for the simultaneous analysis of nickel and cobalt using a virtual chemical spectrophotometer. This involves the use of machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the arXiv categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of a neural network model, which is also relevant to the arXiv category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of a logistic activation function, which is relevant to the arXiv category of cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of absorbance readings, which is relevant to the arXiv category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
